HEADWORD: Wartwort
<hw>Wart"wort`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
name given to several plants because they were thought to be a cure for
warts, as a kind of spurge (<spn>Euphorbia Helioscopia</spn>), and the
nipplewort (<spn>Lampsana communis</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Warty</ent>⟦br⟧
